Kenya Kwanza presidential candidate William Ruto on Wednesday led campaigns inÂ  Bonchari in Kisii County. The UDA leader was accompanied by Kenya Kwanza principals led by Musalia Mudavadi (ANC), Moses Wetangula (Ford Kenya), Joash Maangi (Kisii Deputy Governor) and MP South Mugirango Silvanus Osoro. Lawyer Cliff Ombeta who is vying for the Bonchari parliamentary seat on the UDA ticket was present. Ruto said the Alliance will pioneer a system that will support business enterprises and addresses their challenges. "This is part of our plan to drive business growth to support more families and individuals," he said.